title: Clash breaks out between DU students and ABVP members - The Hindu

organizations.name: ramjas college to maurice nagar police station

text:
February 22, 2017 14:54 IST Updated: February 22, 2017 15:00 IST more-in 
Clashes broke out between the ABVP and students of Delhi University outside Ramjas College on Wednesday. 
Delhi University students had called for a protest march from Ramjas College to Maurice Nagar Police Station. but they were not allowed to leave after gathering inside the college. 
Meanwhile, members of the ABVP, who had entered college in the morning, started assaulting the students and those who did not have ID cards to enter college started shouting slogans against the ABVP. 
Police resorted to lathi charge to control the situation. No one has have detained yet in connection with the incident.
